OL,6,FHe said he took the decision to allow
OL,7,Fall sides to "express their views" and
OL,8,Fthat he was "very, very concerned
OL,9,Fabout the security" of MPs who have
OL,10,Freceived personal threats over their .
OL,12,FBut SNP Westminster leader Stephen
OL,13,FFlynn said he would take significant
OL,14,Fconvincing that the Speaker's position
OL,15,Fwas "not now intolerable" and claimed
OL,16,Fhis party had been treated with
OL,17,F"complete and utter contempt".
